{"article_id":"yUPL7ka8l4qhStbF","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"LISTEN TO ARTICLE 5:58","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"SHARE THIS ARTICLE","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"Share Tweet","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Post Email","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"The Trump administration is considering an order","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"to block the entry of migrants at the southern border ,","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"using the same authority as its earlier travel ban ,","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"a person familiar with the matter said ,","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"as thousands of Central Americans make their way toward the U.S .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"The action ,","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"if implemented ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"would effectively bar those","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"seeking asylum","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"from entering the country .","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"President Donald Trump is weighing a range of options","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"designed to prevent undocumented migrants from crossing the U.S.-Mexican frontier ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"said a White House official familiar with the discussions .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"Both people spoke on condition of anonymity","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"as no final decision has been made .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"The travel ban ,","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"announced shortly after Trump took office in 2017 ,","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"affected people from seven countries , five of them with Muslim majorities .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"The executive order","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"now being looked at","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"would deny asylum claims","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"based on national security concerns ,","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"and would give broad authority to officials at the border ,","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"the person said .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"The New York Times reported late Thursday","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"that the administration was considering an order","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"that would bar migrants ,","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"including those","depth":14},{"id":32,"text":"requesting asylum ,","depth":14},{"id":33,"text":"who try to enter the country from Mexico ,","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"a significant escalation of presidential power on immigration policy .","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"The White House official wouldn ' t confirm the Times report and others ,","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"saying","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"that several legal , executive and legislative remedies were on the table .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"Trump has made undocumented immigration a front-burner issue in the weeks before the midterm congressional elections on Nov. 6 .","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"He ' s blamed Democrats for the so-called caravan of Central American migrants","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"headed through Mexico","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"after starting off in Honduras .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"\" Every time you see a Caravan , or people illegally coming ,","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"or attempting to come , into our Country illegally ,","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"think of and blame the Democrats , \"","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"Trump said Oct. 22 on Twitter , one of three tweets this week","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"referencing the caravan .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"Trump also claimed","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"that \" unknown Middle Easterners \" were blended in with the thousands of Central Americans ,","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"but later said","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"that there was no evidence","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"to support that assertion .","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"The Trump administration plans to send at least 800 additional troops to the U.S.-Mexico border ,","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"according to a third person familiar with the deliberations .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"The Defense Department and Department of Homeland Security confirmed late Friday","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"plans for U.S. Northern Command to send more troops to the border ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"without saying how many .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"In a joint statement , the departments said","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"soldiers will help with planning , engineering support","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"-- such as \" temporary barriers , barricades , and fencing \" --","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"and support for Custom and Border Protection agents","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"including providing them with aircraft , medical teams , temporary housing and protective equipment .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"Where Now for Migrant Caravan","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"as Trump Tweets Threats :","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"QuickTake","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"The president has also threatened to cut off U.S. aid to three Central American countries","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"-- Guatemala , Honduras and El Salvador --","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"over the migrants","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"heading toward the U.S .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"The Times article ,","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"citing sources","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"it didn ' t identify ,","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"that details of the possible executive order were still in the planning stages","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"and that whatever emerged was sure to be met with legal challenges .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"Officials at the National Immigration Law Center ,","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"which participated in the earlier legal challenge to Trump ' s travel ban ,","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"said","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"it is prepared to fight a new order","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"if Trump moves ahead .","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"Marielena Hincapie , executive director of the center , said","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"that the White House ' s consideration of such action shows","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"that Trump ' s \" racism-driven cruelty has no bounds . \"","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"\" We will use every tool","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"to stop Trump from undermining the Constitution and international laws","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"and from instituting his administration ' s agenda","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"to impose a Latin ban in any form , \"","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"Hincapie said in a statement .","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"American Civil Liberties Union immigration rights director Omar Jadwat said","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"it was \" disgraceful \" that the administration \" would even consider what ' s being reported . \"","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"\" It would mean refusing to protect people","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"who can prove","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"they are fleeing persecution , \"","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"Jadwat said in a statement .","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"\" That would be a huge moral failure","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"and any plan along these lines will be subject to intense legal scrutiny . \"","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"But Peter Spiro , an immigration law professor at Temple University , said","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"that courts could uphold the president ' s potential actions .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"In June , a sharply divided Supreme Court upheld Trump ' s ban on travel from the seven countries .","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"The restrictions indefinitely bar more than 150 million people from entering the U.S .","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"\" Most experts would agree about the restrictions","depth":15},{"id":101,"text":"now being contemplated :","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"they make no sense from a policy perspective , \"","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"Spiro said .","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"\" But","depth":13},{"id":105,"text":"just because a ban on asylum applicants would be stupid and cruel","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"doesn ' t mean the Supreme Court would strike it down . \"","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"The troops","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"that Trump is sending to the border","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"would join 2,100 National Guard troops","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"who were previously deployed","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"to perform support duties for Department of Homeland Security personnel .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"Trump said on Twitter on Thursday","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"that he was \" bringing out the military for this National Emergency \"","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"and promised","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"immigrants","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"unlawfully crossing the border","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"\" will be stopped ! \"","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"Earlier :","depth":4},{"id":119,"text":"Trump Gambles With Immigration Attack","depth":5},{"id":120,"text":"to Spur Midterm Voters","depth":5},{"id":121,"text":"Cutting aid to the Central American countries is complicated .","depth":5},{"id":122,"text":"Much of the money for El Salvador , Guatemala , and Honduras was appropriated by Congress in the form of anti-corruption and good-governance programs .","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"Those initiatives have broad support from lawmakers ,","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"who ' ve already promised to put up a fight","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"should Trump try to make good on his threat .","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"The migrants began crossing into southern Mexico on Oct. 20 ,","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"avoiding that country ' s migration authorities and federal police","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"by jumping off the border bridge","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"crossing the Suchiate River ,","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"or by crossing the river in improvised rafts","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"made of tires and boards ,","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"according to images from El Financiero TV .","depth":6},{"id":133,"text":"Under standard U.S. procedures , the migrants ,","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"assuming","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"they reached and attempted to cross the U.S. border ,","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"would be detained","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"for not having the required documents ,","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"and asked","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"whether they ' re afraid of returning to their home .","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"A person","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"who answered \" no \"","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"would not be admitted into the U.S.","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"One","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"who expressed fear of persecution or torture","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"would be interviewed by an asylum officer","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"to establish","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"whether there is credible fear of persecution .","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"Michael J . Bars , a spokesman for the U.S . Citizenship and Immigration Services , said in an email","depth":7},{"id":149,"text":"that the \" extremely low bar \"","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"for establishing credible fear","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"allows economic migrants to abuse the system","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"by posing as asylum seekers ,","depth":9},{"id":153,"text":"then disappear before their court dates","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"to live illegally in the U.S .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":309,"left":0,"right":308,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":308,"left":271,"right":307,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":271,"left":191,"right":270,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":191,"left":157,"right":190,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":157,"left":1,"right":156,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":156,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":190,"left":171,"right":189,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":166,"